      <w:pPr>
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cs="Arial"/>
          <w:color w:val="EE0000"/>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"/>
        </w:rPr>
      </w:pPr>
      <w:r>
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cs="Arial"/>
          <w:color w:val="0000FF"/>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"/>
        </w:rPr>
        <w:t>[Delete personnel categories that are not used]</w:t>
      </w:r>
      <w:r>
        <w:rPr>
          <w:rFonts w:cs="Arial"/>
          <w:szCs w:val="22"/>
        </w:rPr>
        <w:t xml:space="preserve"> </w:t>
      </w:r>
      <w:r>
        <w:t>Labor costs for participating faculty and staff are projected costs based on actual monthly salaries for the university calendar year ending 12/31. Labor costs for post docs are based on projected monthly salaries paid by the participating academic departments at ISU. Graduate students receive a stipend based on annual, full or partial academic semester, or summer paid in equal monthly payments. The ISU Graduate College sets the minimum rates for post docs, and rates and appointment start and end dates for graduate students. Undergraduate wages are based on hourly rates typically paid to upper-level undergraduate research assistants in the College of Agriculture and Life Sciences at ISU.</w:t>
      </w:r>
      
      
      
      
    </w:p>
